    "241621": {
      "transcribe": "Aha, you're bringing up consciousness as a requirement for thinking. That's interesting. There's no way to refute that with any proof. Of course, we don't know exactly what consciousness is and what its role is in intelligence or in thinking. But of course, there are counter arguments that can be given for thinking and consciousness. But yeah, definitely an interesting point. Yep. Simple innovation is definitely something we can expect from AI in 5, 10, and 100 years. I don't know if it's going to take a hundred years to conquer cancer. My hope is it'll take much less time than that. Let's hope in the next 5 to 10 years. Programmers, 5 to 10 years. I don't know. It seems like programming is going to go away. Programming is going to go away or should go away in the next two years. But yeah, maybe you're right because programmers will stick around because there's so much code already written, legacy code that needs to be maintained. Yeah, good question about what's stopping AI from developing self-consciousness. Thank you.",
      "polish": "",
      "polishTranscribeEnd": 0,
      "exportPreferred": null
    },
